  <sect2>
    <title>Installation</title>

    <para>
      Install cURL by running the following commands:
    </para>

<screen><userinput>./configure --prefix=/usr \
            --disable-static \
            --enable-threaded-resolver &amp;&amp;
make</userinput></screen>

    <para>
      Now, as the <systemitem class="username">root</systemitem> user:
    </para>

<screen role="root"><userinput>make install</userinput></screen>

    <sect3>
      <title>Command Explanations</title>

      <para>
        <parameter>--enable-threaded-resolver</parameter>: This switch enables
        cURL's builtin threaded DNS resolver.
      </para>

      <para>
        <option>--with-gssapi</option>: This parameter adds Kerberos 5 support
        to <filename class="libraryfile">libcurl</filename>.
      </para>

    </sect3>

  </sect2>

